IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE ATHLETIC EDUCATION AND TRAINING FOR YOUNG ATHLETES
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE ATHLETIC EDUCATION AND TRAINING FOR YOUNG ATHLETES FROM U6-U23
IRS990.Desc: SACRAMENTO UNITED SOCCER CLUB, INC. ORGANIZED AND TRAINED 18 GIRLS TEAMS AND 21 BOYS TEAMS, COMPRISED OF 510 CHILDREN. THESE TEAMS ENJOYED A YEAR-ROUND PROGRAM OF CLUB-WIDE AND TEAM TRAINING SESSIONS AND CLINICS. THEY ALSO PARTICIPATED IN SPRING, SUMMER, WINTER, AND FALL PLAYING LEAGUES. THE CLUB HOSTED EIGHT TOURNAMENTS AND JAMBOREES TO PROVIDE COMPETITIVE OPPORTUNITIES IN WHICH THE CHILDREN COULD TEST THEIR SKILLS AND DEVELOPMENT AS TEAMS. THE TOURNAMENTS, JAMBOREES, AND OTHER FUNDRAISING EVENTS ALSO GENERATED SUPPLEMENTAL INCOME TO FUND THE CLUB'S SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM AND FIELD DEVELOPMENT NEEDS.PROVIDED NO CHARGE TRAINING OPPORTUNITIES THROUGHOUT THE YEAR FOR CHILDREN TO IMPROVE THEIR SKILLS AND PERSONAL DEVELOPMENT. THESE TRAININGS TOOK PLACE IN VARIOUS NEIGHBORHOODS THROUGHOUT THE CITY ON MOST FRIDAY EVENINGS. MANY OF OUR COACHES VOLUNTEERED TO HELP TRAIN PLAYERS IN RECREATIONAL PROGRAMS.WINTER CAMP WAS OPEN TO ALL YOUTH PLAYERS PROVIDED AT NO CHARGE. SUMMER TEAM CAMP WAS OPEN TO ALL SACRAMENTO UNITED PLAYERS AT NO CHARGE.
